</FONT>
	AND AGREES THAT NOTHING IN THIS AGREEMENT OR ANY OTHER LOAN DOCUMENT WILL AFFECT THE RIGHT OF ANY PARTY HERETO TO SERVE PROCESS IN ANY OTHER MANNER PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	16.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;MARGIN-LEFT:54PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Cross-Guaranty of Co-Borrowers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0.96%;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	16.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;MARGIN-LEFT:94PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Cross-Guaranty.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;Each Co-Borrower hereby agrees that such Co-Borrower is jointly and severally liable for, and hereby absolutely and unconditionally guarantees to Lender and its successors and assigns, the full and prompt payment (whether at stated maturity, by acceleration or otherwise) and performance of, all Obligations owed or hereafter owing to Lender by each other Co-Borrower.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each Co-Borrower agrees that its guaranty obligation hereunder is a continuing guaranty of payment and performance and not of collection, that its obligations under this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	shall not be discharged until payment and performance, in full, of the Obligations has occurred, and that its obligations under this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	shall be absolute and unconditional, irrespective of, and unaffected by:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:2.88%;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(a)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:139PT;">
</FONT>
	the genuineness, validity, regularity, enforceability or any future amendment of, or change in, this Agreement, any other Loan Document or any other agreement, document or instrument to which any Co-Borrower is or may become a party;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:2.88%;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(b)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:139PT;">
</FONT>
	the absence of any action to enforce this Agreement (including this
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16
</FONT>
	) or any other Loan Document, or the waiver or consent by Lender with respect to any of the provisions hereof or thereof;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:2.88%;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(c)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:139PT;">
</FONT>
	the existence, value or condition of, or failure to perfect its Lien against, any security for the Obligations or any action, or the absence of any action, by Lender in respect thereof (including the release of any such security);
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:2.88%;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(d)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:139PT;">
</FONT>
	the insolvency of any Co-Borrower or any other Person; or
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:2.88%;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(e)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:139PT;">
</FONT>
	any other action or circumstances that might otherwise constitute a legal or equitable discharge or defense of a surety or guarantor.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Each Co-Borrower shall be regarded, and shall be in the same position, as principal debtor with respect to the Obligations guaranteed hereunder.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0.96%;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="VTVT-EX1017_589_HTM__TOC260407990">
</A>
<A NAME="VTVT-EX1017_589_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU56">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	16.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;MARGIN-LEFT:94PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Waivers by Co-Borrowers.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;Each Co-Borrower expressly waives all rights it may have now or in the future under any statute, at common law, at law, in equity or otherwise,
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	54

<A NAME="eolPage174"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0.96%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	to compel Lender to mars
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	hal assets or to proceed in respect of the Obligations guaranteed hereunder against any other Co-Borrower, any other party or against any security for the payment and performance of the Obligations before proceeding against, or as a condition to proceeding
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	against, such Co-Borrower.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each Co-Borrower and the Lender agrees that the foregoing waivers are of the essence of the transaction contemplated by this Agreement and the other Loan Documents and that, but for the provisions of this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	and such wa
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	ivers, Lender would decline to enter into this Agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0.96%;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;Each Co-Borrower agrees that the provisions of this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	are for the benefit of Lender and its successors, transferees, endorsees and assigns, and nothing herein contained shall impair, as between any other Co-Borrower and the Lender, the obligations of such other Co-Borrower under the Loan Documents.

</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0.96%;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	16.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;MARGIN-LEFT:94PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Waiver of Subrogation, Etc.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Agreement or in any other Loan Document, and except as set forth in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	, each Co-Borrower hereby expressly and irrevocably waives any and all rights at law or in equity to subrogation, reimbursement, exoneration, contribution, indemnification or set off and any and all defenses available to a surety, guarantor or accommodation co-obligor until the Obligations are indefeasibly paid in full in cash.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each Co-Borrower acknowledges and agrees that this waiver is intended to benefit Lender and shall not limit or otherwise affect such Co-Borrower&#8217;s liability hereunder or the enforceability of this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	, and that Lender and its successors and assigns are intended third party beneficiaries of the waivers and agreements set forth in this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0.96%;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="VTVT-EX1017_589_HTM__TOC260407993">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	16.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;MARGIN-LEFT:94PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Election of Remedies.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;If Lender may, under applicable law, proceed to realize its benefits under any of the Loan Documents giving Lender a Lien upon any Collateral, whether owned by any Co-Borrower or by any other Person, either by judicial foreclosure or by non-judicial sale or enforcement, Lender may, at its sole option, determine which of its remedies or rights it may pursue without affecting any of its rights and remedies under this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;If, in the exercise of any of its rights and remedies, Lender shall forfeit any of its rights or remedies (including, without limitation, its right to enter a deficiency judgment against any Co-Borrower or any other Person), whether because of any applicable laws pertaining to &#8220;election of remedies&#8221; or the like, each Co-Borrower hereby consents to such action by Lender and waives any claim based upon such action, even if such action by Lender shall result in a full or partial loss of any rights of subrogation that each Co-Borrower might otherwise have had but for such action by Lender.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any election of remedies that results in the denial or impairment of the right of Lender to seek a deficiency judgment against any Co-Borrower shall not impair any other Co-Borrower&#8217;s obligation to pay the full amount of the Obligations.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event Lender shall bid at any foreclosure or trustee&#8217;s sale or at any private sale permitted by law or the Loan Documents, Lender may bid all or less than the amount of the Obligations and the amount of such bid need not be paid by Lender but shall be credited against the Obligations.&nbsp;&nbsp;The amount of the successful bid at any such sale, whether a Lender or any other party is the successful bidder, shall be conclusively deemed to be the fair market value of the Collateral and the difference between such bid amount and the remaining balance of the Obligations shall be conclusively deemed to be the amount of the Obligations guaranteed under this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	, notwithstanding that any present or future law or court decision or ruling may have the effect of reducing the amount of any deficiency claim to which Lender might otherwise be entitled but for such bidding at any such sale.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	55

	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0.96%;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="VTVT-EX1017_589_HTM__TOC260407994">
</A>
<A NAME="VTVT-EX1017_589_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU57">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	16.6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;MARGIN-LEFT:94PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Limitation.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	Notwithstanding any provision herein contained to the contrary, each Co-Borrower&#8217;s liability under this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	(which liability i
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	s in any event in addition to amounts for which such Co-Borrower is primarily liable under this Agreement) shall be limited to an amount not to exceed as of any date of determination the lesser of:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:2.88%;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(a)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:139PT;">
</FONT>
	the net amount of all Loans advanced to any other Co-Borrower under this Agreement and then re-loaned or otherwise transferred to, or for the benefit of, such Co-Borrower; and
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:2.88%;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(b)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:139PT;">
</FONT>
	the amount that could be claimed by Lender from such Co-Borrower under this
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
	without rendering such claim voidable or avoidable under Section&#160;548 of the Bankruptcy Code or under any applicable state Uniform Fraudulent Transfer Act, Uniform Fraudulent Conveyance Act or similar statute or common law after taking into account, among other things, such Co-Borrower&#8217;s right of contribution and indemnification from each other Co-Borrower under
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16.7
</FONT>
	.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0.96%;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="VTVT-EX1017_589_HTM__TOC260407995">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	16.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;MARGIN-LEFT:94PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Contribution with Respect to Guaranty Obligations.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:2.88%;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(a)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:139PT;">
</FONT>
	To the extent that any Co-Borrower shall make a payment under this
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16
</FONT>
	of all or any of the Obligations (other than Loans made to such Co-Borrower for which it is primarily liable) (a &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Guarantor&#160;Payment
</FONT>
	&#8221;) that, taking into account all other Guarantor Payments then previously or concurrently made by any other Co-Borrower, exceeds the amount that such Co-Borrower would otherwise have paid if each Co-Borrower had paid the aggregate Obligations satisfied by such Guarantor Payment in the same proportion that such Co-Borrower&#8217;s &#8220;Allocable Amount&#8221; (as defined below) (as determined immediately prior to such Guarantor Payment) bore to the aggregate Allocable Amounts of each of the Co-Borrowers as determined immediately prior to the making of such Guarantor Payment, then, following indefeasible payment in full in cash of the Obligations and termination of the commitments to lend hereunder, such Co-Borrower shall be entitled to receive contribution and indemnification payments from, and be reimbursed by, each other Co-Borrower for the amount of such excess, pro rata based upon their respective Allocable Amounts in effect immediately prior to such Guarantor Payment.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:2.88%;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="VTVT-EX1017_589_HTM__REF149519801">
</A>
	(b)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:139PT;">
</FONT>
	As of any date of determination, the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Allocable Amount
</FONT>
	&#8221; of any Co-Borrower shall be equal to the maximum amount of the claim that could then be recovered from such Co-Borrower under this
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16
</FONT>
	without rendering such claim voidable or avoidable under Section&#160;548 of the Bankruptcy Code or under any applicable state Uniform Fraudulent Transfer Act, Uniform Fraudulent Conveyance Act or similar statute or common law.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:2.88%;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(c)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:139PT;">
</FONT>
	This
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16.7
</FONT>
	is intended only to define the relative rights of Co-Borrowers and nothing set forth in this
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16.7
</FONT>
	is intended to or shall impair the obligations of Co-Borrowers, jointly and severally, to pay any amounts as and when the same shall become due and payable in accordance with the terms of this Agreement.&nbsp;&nbsp;Nothing contained in this
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16.7
</FONT>
	shall limit the liability of any Co-Borrower to pay the Loans made directly or indirectly to such Co-Borrower and accrued interest, fees and expenses with respect thereto for which such Co-Borrower shall be primarily liable.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	56
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage176"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:2.88%;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="VTVT-EX1017_589_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU58">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(d)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:139PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The parties hereto acknowledge that the rights of contribution and indemnification hereunder shall constitute assets of the Co-Borrowers to which such contribution and indemnification is owing.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:2.88%;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(e)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:139PT;">
</FONT>
	The rights of the indemnifying Co-Borrowers against other Co-Borrowers under this
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16
</FONT>
	shall be exercisable upon the full and indefeasible payment of the Obligations and the termination of the commitments to lend hereunder.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0.96%;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="VTVT-EX1017_589_HTM__TOC260407996">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	16.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;MARGIN-LEFT:94PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Liability Cumulative.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;The liability of Co-Borrowers under this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	is in addition to and shall be cumulative with all liabilities of each Co-Borrower to the Lender under this Agreement and the other Loan Documents to which such Co-Borrower is a party or in respect of any Obligations or obligation of the other Co-Borrower, without any limitation as to amount, unless the instrument or agreement evidencing or creating such other liability specifically provides to the contrary.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	[Remainder of page intentionally left blank.]

	FUNDING CERTIFICATE

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The undersigned, being the duly elected and acting
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

	of vTv THERAPEUTICS, INC. a Delaware corporation (&#8220;Borrower Representative&#8221;), does hereby certify to HORIZON TECHNOLOGY FINANCE CORPORATION (&#8220;Horizon&#8221;) and SILICON VALLEY BANKS(&#8220;SVB&#8221;, and collectively with Horizon, the &#8220;Lenders&#8221;) in connection with that certain Venture Loan and Security Agreement dated as of August __, 2016 by and among Borrower Representative, vTv Therapeutics LLC, Lenders and Horizon as Collateral Agent (the &#8220;Loan Agreement&#8221;; with other capitalized terms used below having the meanings ascribed thereto in the Loan Agreement) that:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.41%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	1.

	The representations and warranties made by each Co-Borrower in
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">

	of the Loan Agreement and in the other Loan Documents are true and correct as of the date hereof.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.41%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.

	of the Loan Agreement to the making of the Loan to be made on or about the date hereof have been satisfied.

	5.

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(Loan [&nbsp;&nbsp; ])
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	$____________________
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	Dated:&nbsp;&nbsp;August __, 2016
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.41%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	FOR VALUE RECEIVED, the undersigned, vTv THERAPEUTICS INC., a Delaware corporation (&#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Borrower Representative
</FONT>
	&#8221;) and vTv THERAPEUTICS LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (&#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	vTv LLC
</FONT>
	&#8221; and collectively with Borrower Representative, &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Co-Borrowers
</FONT>
	&#8221;), HEREBY JOINTLY AND SEVERALLY PROMISE TO PAY to [HORIZON TECHNOLOGY FINANCE CORPORATION, a Delaware corporation[/[SILICON VALLEY BANK, a California corporation] (&#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Lender
</FONT>
	&#8221;) the principal amount of ____________ Dollars ($__________) or such lesser amount as shall equal the outstanding principal balance of Loan [&nbsp;&nbsp; ] (the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Loan
</FONT>
	&#8221;) made to Co-Borrowers by Lender pursuant to the Loan Agreement (as defined below), and to pay all other amounts due with respect to the Loan on the dates and in the amounts set forth in the Loan Agreement. Capitalized terms used but not defined herein shall have the meaning ascribed thereto in the Loan Agreement.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.41%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Interest on the principal amount of this Note from the date of this Note shall accrue at the Loan Rate or, if applicable, the Default Rate, each as established in accordance with the Loan Agreement (as defined below).&nbsp;&nbsp;Interest shall be computed on the basis of a 360-day year for the actual number of days elapsed.&nbsp;&nbsp;If the Funding Date is not the first day of the month, interim interest accruing from the Funding Date through the last day of that month shall be paid on the first calendar day of the next calendar month.&nbsp;&nbsp;Commencing [_], 201[_], through and including [_], 201[_], on the first day of each month (each an &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Interest Payment Date
</FONT>
	&#8221;) Co-Borrowers shall make payments of accrued interest only on the outstanding principal amount of the Loan.&nbsp;&nbsp;Commencing on [_], 201[_], and continuing on the first day of each month thereafter (each a &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Principal and Interest Payment Date
</FONT>
	&#8221; and, collectively with each Interest Payment Date, each a &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Payment Date
</FONT>
	&#8221;), Co-Borrowers shall make to Lender twenty-four (24) equal payments of principal in the amount of&nbsp;&nbsp;[______________] plus accrued interest on the then outstanding principal amount due hereunder. On the earliest to occur of (i) [_], 201[_], (ii) payment in full of the principal balance of the Loan or (iii) an Event of Default and demand by Lender of payment in full of the Loan, Co-Borrowers shall make a payment of [_] and 00/100 Dollars ($[_]) to Lender (the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Final Payment
</FONT>
	&#8221;). If not sooner paid, all outstanding amounts hereunder and under the Loan Agreement shall become due and payable on [_], 201[_].
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.41%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Principal, interest and all other amounts due with respect to the Loan, are payable in lawful money of the United States of America to Lender as set forth in the Loan Agreement.&nbsp;&nbsp;The principal amount of this Note and the interest rate applicable thereto, and all payments made with respect thereto, shall be recorded by Lender and, prior to any transfer hereof, endorsed on the grid attached hereto which is part of this Note.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.41%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	This Note is referred to in, and is entitled to the benefits of, the Venture Loan and Security Agreement dated as of August __, 2016 (the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Loan Agreement
</FONT>
	&#8221;), among Co-Borrowers, Lender and [Horizon Technology Finance Corporation][Silicon Valley Bank].&nbsp;&nbsp;The Loan Agreement, among other things, (a) provides for the making of a secured Loan to Co-Borrowers, and (b) contains provisions for acceleration of the maturity hereof upon the happening of certain stated events.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">

	Co-Borrowers shall pay all fees and expenses, including reasonable attorneys&#8217; fees and costs, incurred by Lender in the enforcement or attempt to enforce any Co-Borrower&#8217;s obligations hereunder not performed when due.&nbsp;&nbsp;

	Any reference herein to Lender shall be deemed to include and apply to every subsequent holder of this Note.&nbsp;&nbsp;Reference is made to the Loan Agreement for provisions concerning optional and mandatory prepayments, Collateral, acceleration and other material terms affecting this Note.

	This Note shall be governed by and construed under the laws of the State of New York.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each Co-Borrower agrees that any action or proceeding brought to enforce or arising out of this Note may be commenced in the Supreme Court of the State of New York, Borough of Manhattan, or in the District Court of the United Stated for the Southern District of New York.

<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	EXHIBIT F
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	CLINICAL END POINTS FOR PHASE III CLINICAL TRIAL OF TTP488
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMESNEWROMAN;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The STEADFAST Study is a multi-center, randomized, double-blind, placebo-controlled, parallel-group study evaluating the efficacy and safety of 18 months of treatment with
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	azeliragon
</FONT>
	relative to placebo conducted in approximately 800 mild AD patients (Parts A and B) who are on background standard of care.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMESNEWROMAN;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Primary Endpoints:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMESNEWROMAN,ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Co-primary Endpoints:
</P>

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	QUALIFYING TERM SHEET
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Qualifying Term Sheet
</FONT>
	&#8221; means a fully-executed term sheet for the licensing sale, co-development, co-commercialization, or other transfer of a drug compound or program, which term sheet:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(a)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:76PT;">
</FONT>
	for the glukokinase activator program, including the TTP399 drug compound, or the GLP1-R program, including the TTP273 drug compound, requires either (i) a cash payment to Co-Borrowers upon the closing of such transaction of not less than [***], or (ii) both (x) a cash payment to Co-Borrowers upon the closing of such transaction of not less than [***] and (y) clinical milestone payments to Co-Borrowers of not less than [***];&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(b)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:76PT;">
</FONT>
	for the receptor for advanced glycation endproducts program, including the TTP488 drug compound, requires either (i) a cash payment to Co-Borrowers upon the closing of such transaction of not less than [***], or (ii) requires both (x) a cash payment to Co-Borrowers upon the closing of such transaction of not less than [***] and (y) clinical milestone payments to Co-Borrowers of not less than [***]; or&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:10.58%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(c)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:76PT;">
</FONT>
	is otherwise acceptable to Lenders in their sole discretion.
</P>

	CERTIFICATION PURSUANT TO

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
